  "why": "The paper applies image-level transformations (brightness, contrast, blur, rotation, etc.) that are less sensitive to serialization-induced precision loss and it constrains parameter ranges via manually tuned domains and SSIM-based filtering. However, it does not explicitly describe enforcing input format serialization constraints (e.g., clipping to integer [0,255] pixel values or rounding) or generating inputs directly in a serialized format. Thus the mutations are of the kind less likely to be removed by serialization but there is no explicit handling of rounding/clipping to guarantee failure reproducibility after saving.",
